# i18n Rule — Every Visible String Must Use the Translation System

This project supports 12 languages. Switching language in Settings must instantly update **every** visible character in the UI — labels, placeholders, tooltips, empty states, date names, error messages, section headers, dropdown options, everything.

**Never write a raw string literal where the user can read it.**

---

## 1. How the Translation System Works

| File | Role |
|---|---|
| `frontend/src/contexts/LanguageContext.tsx` | Single source of truth — all keys live here |
| `MESSAGES.de` | German (primary/default) |
| `MESSAGES.en` | English |
| `MESSAGES.fr` | French |
| `LANGUAGE_OVERRIDES.{es,it,pt,tr,ru,hi,ar,zh,ja}` | Merge over `en` for 9 other languages |

### Hook usage

```tsx
// In pages, components, widgets — always call the hook at the top
const { t, language } = useLanguage();

// In widgets that might need the active language tag (e.g. for Intl)
const { t, language } = useWidgetLanguage(); // equivalent, use either
```

---

## 2. Core Rules (apply to every file you touch)

### Rule 1 — No hardcoded text in JSX

Every string the user sees must go through `t()`.

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT
<p>{t("tasksEmpty", "No tasks yet")}</p>
<input placeholder={t("searchPlaceholder", "Search…")} />
<button title={t("commonClose", "Close")} />

// ❌ WRONG
<p>No tasks yet</p>
<p>Keine Aufgaben</p>
<input placeholder="Suchen…" />
```

### Rule 2 — Always add keys to all 3 primary languages

When you add a new key, add it to **`MESSAGES.de`**, **`MESSAGES.en`**, and **`MESSAGES.fr`** in `LanguageContext.tsx`. The other 9 languages inherit from `en` automatically (add overrides if a specific translation is needed).

```ts
// In MESSAGES.de:
myNewKey: "Deutscher Text",

// In MESSAGES.en:
myNewKey: "English text",

// In MESSAGES.fr:
myNewKey: "Texte français",
```

### Rule 3 — Always use English as the fallback, never German

The second argument to `t()` is the fallback shown when the key is missing. It must be English.

```tsx
// ✅
t("tabOverdue", "Overdue")
t("commonSave", "Save")

// ❌ German fallback = German shown for missing keys
t("tabOverdue", "Überfällig")
```

### Rule 4 — Label arrays must live inside `useMemo`, never as module-level constants

Any array or object that contains user-visible labels must be created inside the component using `useMemo` so it re-evaluates when the language changes.

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT — reactive
const tabs = useMemo(() => [
  { id: "today", label: t("tabToday", "Today") },
  { id: "week",  label: t("tabWeek",  "This week") },
], [t]);

// ❌ WRONG — static, never updates
const TABS = [
  { id: "today", label: "Heute" },
];
```

### Rule 5 — Relative time and formatted date strings must use `t()`

```tsx
// ✅
t("relTimeJustNow", "Just now")
t("relTimeMins", "{n} min ago").replace("{n}", String(mins))

// ❌
"Gerade eben"
`vor ${mins} Min.`
```

---

## 3. Locale-Aware Date/Time Formatting

Never hardcode locale strings like `"de-DE"`. Derive the BCP-47 locale tag from `language`:

```tsx
const { language } = useLanguage();

const localeTag = language === "de" ? "de-DE"
  : language === "fr" ? "fr-FR"
  : language === "es" ? "es-ES"
  : language === "it" ? "it-IT"
  : language === "pt" ? "pt-PT"
  : language === "tr" ? "tr-TR"
  : language === "ru" ? "ru-RU"
  : language === "ar" ? "ar-SA"
  : language === "zh" ? "zh-CN"
  : language === "ja" ? "ja-JP"
  : language === "hi" ? "hi-IN"
  : "en-GB";
```

Use `Intl.DateTimeFormat` with `localeTag` for month/weekday names — never hardcode them:

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT — automatically adapts to selected language
const monthNames = useMemo(() =>
  Array.from({ length: 12 }, (_, i) =>
    new Intl.DateTimeFormat(localeTag, { month: "long" }).format(new Date(2000, i, 1))
  ), [localeTag]);

// ❌ WRONG — only ever shows German
const MONTHS_DE = ["Januar", "Februar", "März", …];
```

Pass `localeTag` to `toLocaleDateString()` calls too:

```tsx
// ✅
new Date(iso).toLocaleDateString(localeTag, { weekday: "short", day: "2-digit", month: "short" })

// ❌
new Date(iso).toLocaleDateString("de-DE", …)
```

---

## 4. Component-Specific Patterns

### DatePickerInput (`src/components/DatePickerInput.tsx`)
- Uses `useLanguage()` internally — do **not** pass locale as a prop
- Month names, short month names, and weekday names are all generated via `Intl.DateTimeFormat`
- UI strings ("Today", "Clear", placeholder) must use `t()` with keys `datePickerToday`, `datePickerClear`, `datePickerPlaceholder`, `datePickerTitle`

### AssigneePicker (`src/widgets/AssigneePicker.tsx`)
- Uses `useLanguage()` internally
- All dropdown header text, workload labels, "Fully booked", "You", footer note → use `t()` with `assign*` key prefix
- Workload level labels come from `WORKLOAD_CONFIG[level].labelKey` — use `t(cfg.labelKey, cfg.label)`
- Workload detail strings use `workload*` key prefix with `{n}` placeholder replacement

### TaskContextFields (`src/widgets/TaskContextFields.tsx`)
- Uses `useLanguage()` internally
- `buildFields()` receives `t` as a parameter and uses it for all `label` and `placeholder` strings
- Keys follow `ctxLabel*` (labels) and `ctxPh*` (placeholders) naming

### TaskFormModal (`src/widgets/TaskFormModal.tsx`)
- Receives `t` as a prop — do not call `useLanguage()` here; use the passed `t`
- All form labels, subtitles, button text must use `t()`

### TasksWidget (`src/widgets/TasksWidget.tsx`)
- Filter tab labels → inside `useMemo`, use `tab*` keys
- Section group headers → inside `useMemo`, use `tasksSection*` keys
- `formatDueDate` receives `t` and uses `dueDateToday` / `dueDateTomorrow` keys
- Task preset labels → `translatedTaskPresets` useMemo using `taskPreset*` keys
- Priority labels → `translatedPriorities` useMemo using `tasksHigh`, `tasksMedium`, `tasksNew`

### workloadStore (`src/store/workloadStore.ts`)
- `WORKLOAD_CONFIG` entries must have a `labelKey` (string) field pointing to a key in MESSAGES
- Never put the translated label directly in the store — translation happens in the component

---

## 5. Key Naming Conventions

Use camelCase with a feature prefix:

| Prefix | Used for |
|---|---|
| `tab*` | Filter tab labels (`tabToday`, `tabOverdue`, `tabAll`) |
| `tasks*` | Task widget strings (`tasksEmpty`, `tasksFieldTitle`) |
| `taskPreset*` | Task type preset names |
| `tasksSection*` | Group/section headers in task lists |
| `notif*` | Notification panel |
| `settings*` | Settings page |
| `common*` | Shared actions (`commonSave`, `commonCancel`, `commonEdit`) |
| `relTime*` | Relative timestamps (`relTimeJustNow`, `relTimeMins`) |
| `dueDate*` | Due date display labels |
| `assign*` | AssigneePicker dropdown strings |
| `workload*` | Workload bar labels and counts |
| `datePicker*` | DatePickerInput UI strings |
| `ctx*` | TaskContextFields field labels and placeholders |

---

## 6. Checklist — Before You Finish Any Edit

- [ ] Every JSX string literal replaced with `t("key", "English fallback")`
- [ ] New keys added to `MESSAGES.de`, `MESSAGES.en`, `MESSAGES.fr`
- [ ] No `"de-DE"` hardcoded anywhere — derive from `language`
- [ ] Label arrays built inside `useMemo`, not as module constants
- [ ] No German text in fallback arguments
- [ ] `toLocaleDateString()` uses `localeTag`, not a hardcoded locale string
